  "notes": [
    "195 ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes covered (representing sovereign nations + partially-recognized states). Non-sovereign territories (e.g. Puerto Rico, Guam, American Samoa) are also included where they have distinct tax regimes from their parent sovereign.",
    "default_rate is the country's DOMINANT rate as of catalogue authoring (2026). Rates change at fiscal-year boundaries; the SyncTaxRatesFromProviderJob pulls current rates from the tenant's configured provider.",
    "registration_format is the regex format for the country's VAT/GST/EIN number. Null when no standardized format exists.",
    "US default_rate is 0.0 because US sales tax is state + local, not federal. State-level jurisdictions seed via a separate ISO 3166-2 subdivision catalogue.",
    "Zero-rated countries (KW, QA, CY, ...) may be zero-VAT but still require registration for large sellers per Wayfair-analogue rules.",
    "The catalogue is seeded as platform-reference tax_jurisdictions with tenant_id IS NULL. Tenants can override country-level rates by adding a tenant-scoped rate row (via /api/v1/tax/rates POST) — the resolver prefers tenant-scoped rates over platform-reference."
  ]
}
